OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1773414683
OL,3,CSpring Clean: Keep, Chuck or Cash In?
OL,5,FAnd Local Authorities and Waste
OL,6,FManagement companies are also getting
OL,7,Fon board with re-using items instead
OL,8,Fof recycling them or throwing them
OL,9,Faway. The Renew Hub in Greater
OL,10,FManchester is a 5000sq ft space run by
OL,11,Fwaste management company Suez for the
OL,12,FGreater Manchester Combined Authority.
OL,13,FHere, 125,000 unwanted household items
OL,14,Fcollected from local recycling centres
OL,15,Fare repaired and upcycled ready to re-
OL,16,Fsold for charity.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1773414683
OL,3,CSpring Clean: Keep, Chuck or Cash In?
OL,5,F"Since we've opened this site in 2021,
OL,6,Fit's about 2 million pounds of funding
OL,7,Fwe've been able to give back through
OL,8,Fthe charities over that period. Re-
OL,9,Fusing material is even better than
OL,10,Frecycling, so it's something we all
OL,11,Fwant to work more and more on. So
OL,12,Fthere's a real design to really drive
OL,13,Fthis type of operation forward."
OL,15,FJohn Scanlon, Vice President, UK, Suez.
OL,26,@mD@AOUuD@`O]
